# MCP Servers Usage

Use MCP servers to fetch up-to-date documentation and code examples.

## Available MCP Servers

| Server | Purpose | Best For |
|--------|---------|----------|
| **context7** | Library/framework docs | Third-party libraries, SDKs, frameworks |
| **exa** | AI-powered web & code search | Real-time web search, code examples, company research |
| **bedrock-agentcore-mcp** | AgentCore platform | Runtime, Memory, Gateway, deployment |
| **aws-documentation-mcp** | Official AWS docs | AWS services, APIs, best practices |

## Priority Order for Different Query Types

### For Library/Framework Documentation
1. **Context7 MCP** - First choice for structured library docs
2. **Exa MCP** (`get_code_context_exa`) - When Context7 lacks the library or need diverse real-world examples
3. **Web Search** - Last resort

### For General Web Search / Real-time Information
1. **Exa MCP** (`web_search_exa`) - First choice, AI-optimized context
2. **Generic WebSearch** - Fallback if Exa unavailable

### For AWS Services
1. **Bedrock AgentCore MCP** - For AgentCore-specific questions (Runtime, Memory, Gateway)
2. **AWS Documentation MCP** - For general AWS services (S3, Lambda, IAM, etc.)
3. **Context7** - For boto3/SDK code examples

### For Company/Business Research
1. **Exa MCP** (`company_research_exa`) - Comprehensive company information

