## Context7 MCP (`user-context7`)

### When to Use
- Questions about libraries, frameworks, SDKs (React, Django, Strands, etc.)
- "How to" questions involving external packages
- Need code examples for a specific technology

### How to Use
1. Call `resolve-library-id` with library name and user's question
2. Select best match (prefer higher Code Snippets + Benchmark Score)
3. Call `query-docs` with specific questions

### Constraints
- **Max 3 calls per question**
- Use specific queries: "How to configure JWT in Express" (good) vs "auth" (bad)

---

## Bedrock AgentCore MCP (`user-bedrock-agentcore-mcp-server`)

### When to Use
- Building or deploying agents with AgentCore Runtime
- Configuring AgentCore Memory (event/semantic memory)
- Setting up AgentCore Gateway (API-to-tool transformation)
- AgentCore Code Interpreter or Browser questions
- Troubleshooting AgentCore deployments

### Available Tools

| Tool | Purpose | Args |
|------|---------|------|
| `search_agentcore_docs` | Search all AgentCore documentation | `query`, `k` (results) |
| `fetch_agentcore_doc` | Fetch full document by URL | `uri` |
| `manage_agentcore_runtime` | Runtime deployment guide | None |
| `manage_agentcore_gateway` | Gateway management guide | None |
| `manage_agentcore_memory` | Memory configuration guide | None |

### How to Use

```
# Search AgentCore docs
search_agentcore_docs: query="deploy agent to runtime", k=5

# Get full document
fetch_agentcore_doc: uri="https://..."

# Get runtime deployment guide (no args needed)
manage_agentcore_runtime

# Get gateway guide (no args needed)
manage_agentcore_gateway

# Get memory guide (no args needed)
manage_agentcore_memory
```

### Coverage
- Platform services: Runtime, Memory, Code Interpreter, Browser, Gateway, Observability, Identity
- Getting started guides and tutorials
- API references (data plane and control APIs)
- Framework integrations: Strands, LangGraph, CrewAI

