## AWS Documentation MCP (`user-awslabs.aws-documentation-mcp-server`)

### When to Use
- Questions about AWS services (S3, Bedrock, Lambda, IAM, etc.)
- AWS API references and best practices
- Finding new features for AWS services
- Troubleshooting AWS configurations

### Available Tools

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `search_documentation` | Search across all AWS docs |
| `read_documentation` | Fetch full page content as markdown |
| `recommend` | Get related docs (Highly Rated, New, Similar, Journey) |

### How to Use

```
# Search for documentation
search_documentation: search_phrase="Bedrock AgentCore deployment", limit=10

# Read a specific page
read_documentation: url="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/...", max_length=5000

# Get recommendations (find new features)
recommend: url="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/service/welcome.html"
```

### Search Tips
- Include service names: "S3 bucket versioning" not just "versioning"
- Use `product_types` filter: `["Amazon Bedrock"]`
- Use `guide_types` filter: `["User Guide", "API Reference"]`

